descript.abstract: The Coastal Island Bird Rookery shapefile dipicts bird rookery locations on the coastal islands of Texas. The file is in progress. Over 130 features were added to an origional file of unknown origin containing 154 features. The update represented in this files includes the additional features, which were digitized based on 2008 naip imagery and ESRIs “ESRI_Imagery_World_2D” online layer.
descript.purpose: The Texas Natural Diversity Database (TXNDD) is a GIS integrated Oracle database which stores spatial and tabular information for: Threatened and Endangered Species, Rare species of concern, Rare natural vegetation communities, and other rare natural resources. It is a collaborative effort manged in part by the Texas Parks and Wildlife, Wildlife Division. The TXNDD builds from The Nature Conservancy developed Natural Heritage Programs from the mid-1970s. It originated in The General Land Office in 1983 and was formerly known as the Biological & Conservation Data system (BCD).
